properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 8:53PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Westerly winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
expected. Wind gusts as high as 80 mph may occur below
Tehachapi Pass in the vicinity of Mojave Sunday evening.

* WHERE...The Kern county mountains and desert.

* WHEN...From 4 PM Sunday to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds can blow down trees, power lines and
any unsecured objects. A few powers outages are possible.
Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roads impacted by strong winds include
Highway 155, Highway 178 through and below Walker Pass,
Highway 58 through and below Tehachapi Pass, Highway 14 in the
vicinity of Mojave and U.S. 395.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM SUNDAY TO NOON PST MONDAY
